                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d319">
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">No. 319.</seg>
                </opener>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">West</persName> to Mr. <persName
                            type="to">Bayard</persName>
                    </hi>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1885-04-28">
                            <hi rend="italic">April</hi> 28, 1885</date>. (Received April
                        29.)</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: With reference to my note of the 18th February
                    last, and to the reply of your predecessor of the 8th January, I have the honor
                    to inform you that Earl Granville has directed me again to request that some
                    decision may be taken in the Tunstall case, which has been pending for the last
                    seven years.</p>
                <p>I have, &amp;c.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>L. S. SACKVILLE-WEST.</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
